===Religion===
Although there is no religious data available separately for Batumi, the majority of the region's inhabitants are [[Eastern Orthodox Christian]], and primarily adhere to the national [[Georgian Orthodox Church]].&lt;ref name=&quot;geostat.ge&quot;&gt;National Statistics Office of Georgia. [http://www.geostat.ge/cms/site_images/_files/english/census/2014/22_Population%20by%20regions%20and%20religion.xls Population Census 2014: Population by Regions and Religion] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160914035909/http://www.geostat.ge/cms/site_images/_files/english/census/2014/22_Population%20by%20regions%20and%20religion.xls |date=September 14, 2016 }}, Retrieved: 6 May 2016&lt;/ref&gt; There are also Sunni [[Islam in Georgia (country)|Muslim]], [[Roman Catholicism in Georgia|Catholic]], [[Armenian Apostolic]], and Jewish communities.&lt;ref name=&quot;geostat.ge&quot;/&gt;

The main places of worship in the city are:
*[[Georgian Orthodox Church|Georgian Orthodox]] [[Batumi Cathedral|Cathedral of the Mother of God]], and [[Saint Barbara]] Church
*[[Roman Catholicism|Catholic]] [[Church of the Holy Spirit (Batumi)|Church of the Holy Spirit]]
*Saint Nicholas Church
*[[Batumi Mosque]]
*[[Batumi Synagogue]]&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url= http://batumi.ge/en/?page=show&amp;sec=75|title= Batumi: sights|publisher= Official website of Batumi|access-date=May 10, 2009}}&lt;/ref&gt;

