== Economy and infrastructure ==

=== Transportation ===
&lt;!-- Image with unknown copyright status removed: [[File:Batumirport.jpg|thumb|left|Batumi|{{Deletable image-caption|1=Wednesday, May 27, 2009|date=March 2012}}]] --&gt;The city is served by [[Batumi Airport]], one of three international airports in the country.&lt;!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Bstumire.jpg|thumb|Batumi International Airport
. {{Deletable image-caption|date=March 2012}}]] --&gt;&lt;!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Bstumireco.jpg|thumb|Batumi International Airport
. {{Deletable image-caption|date=March 2012}}]] --&gt;
A [[bike-sharing]] scheme named ''BatumVelo'' allows you to rent a bicycle on the street with a smart card.

[[File:Batumi seaport, Adjaria, Georgia.jpg|thumb|The seaport of Batumi with the city in the background.]]

The port of Batumi is on one of the routes of China's proposed [[Eurasian Land Bridge]] (part of the &quot;New Silk Road&quot;), which would see an eastern freight link to China via Azerbaijan and the Caspian Sea, and a western link by ferry to Ukraine and on to Europe.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite news|last1=Dyussembekova|first1=Zhazira|title=Silk Road Renewed With Launch of New Commercial Transit Route|url=http://astanatimes.com/2016/01/silk-road-renewed-with-launch-of-new-commercial-transit-route/|work=The Astana Times|date=21 January 2016}}&lt;/ref&gt;

